%% weekly_load orchestration — personal-health-elt
%% The Prefect flow's end-to-end sequence: hash + load CSVs → enrich → dbt build
%% (skipped when nothing new) → notify → Firestore feed. Authoritative:
%% ingest/flows/weekly_load.py. Render: any Mermaid viewer, or GitHub ```mermaid.
%% Maintenance: update when the flow's task order, skip logic, or consumers change.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Cron as launchd + Prefect Cron (Sun 06:00 CT)
    participant Flow as weekly_load flow
    participant Load as batch loader
    participant Enr as weather + calendar loaders
    participant PG as Postgres (raw.*)
    participant Dbt as dbt build
    participant Notify as notifier
    participant FS as Firestore (Tempo)
    participant Push as Pushover

    Note over Flow: @flow retries=1, retry_delay=120s (coarse net over per-task retries)

    Cron->>Flow: trigger weekly_load()

    Flow->>Load: load_drop_folder(RAW_DATA_PATH)
    Note right of Load: @task retries=1, 30s
    loop each new CSV in data/raw/
        Load->>PG: SHA256 in file_inventory?
        alt hash already present
            PG-->>Load: skip file (no-op)
        else new file
            Load->>PG: INSERT rows ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING + file_inventory row (one txn)
        end
    end
    Load-->>Flow: BatchResult (files_loaded, rows_inserted, errors)

    Flow->>Enr: load_weather() then load_calendar()
    Note right of Enr: non-fatal (try/except) — quiet skip if no API key / iCal URL
    Enr->>PG: upsert raw.weather / raw.calendar_daily
    Enr-->>Flow: WeatherResult / CalendarResult

    alt files errored
        Flow-->>Flow: log ERROR, SKIP dbt build (dbt_exit_code=None)
    else 0 new rows (HK + weather + calendar)
        Flow-->>Flow: log "no new rows", SKIP dbt build
    else new data present
        Flow->>Dbt: run_dbt_build()  (subprocess)
        Note right of Dbt: @task retries=2, 60s — logs stderr tail, raises DbtBuildError on non-zero
        Dbt->>PG: rebuild analytics_staging → intermediate → marts + run all tests
        Dbt-->>Flow: exit 0
    end

    Flow->>Notify: notify_state_changes()
    Note right of Notify: non-fatal — reads mart_recovery_state — dedup via notification_log (rule_name, day) PK
    Notify->>PG: read mart + claim (rule, day) row
    Notify->>Push: send (only if rule fired today)
    Notify-->>Flow: NotifyResult (sent, deduped)

    Flow->>FS: push_recovery_state_to_tempo()
    Note right of FS: non-fatal — runs last (needs fresh mart) — quiet skip if Tempo env unset
    FS->>PG: read trailing 14d of mart_recovery_state
    FS->>FS: write users/{uid}/recovery_state/{latest,history}
    FS-->>Flow: PushResult (rows_fetched, skipped)

    Flow-->>Cron: summary dict (counts, dbt_exit_code, notifications, tempo)
